        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-04-25 23:06:43.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-6495 o2iblnd: IB Multi-Rail",
        "message": "LU-6495 o2iblnd: IB Multi-Rail\n\nCode contributed by Fujitsu, documentation below:\n\nSteps to set IB Multi-Rail\n\n0. Setting IB\n============\n\nPlease configure all IB devices in the unique subnet.\nPlease allocate IP address of IPoIB to each IB HCA device.\n\n1. Preparing /etc/sysconfig/lnet_o2ibs.conf configuration file\n====================================================\n\nPlease create the file /etc/sysconfig/lnet_o2ibs.conf in the following format.\n\n192.168.128.10@o2ib0 192.168.128.10 192.168.128.11\n192.168.128.12@o2ib0 192.168.128.12 192.168.128.13\n192.168.128.14@o2ib0 192.168.128.14 192.168.128.15\n\nPlease list all IP addresses of a NID on a single line.\nSet the first column to NID, and then set the second and the following columns to IP addresses.\nPlease describe information about all nodes which have multiple IB HCAs in this file.\n\nPlease describe IP addresses in the order in which the devices are specified in the networks parameter of lnet module.\nFor example, when networks parameter is networks=o2ib0(ib0,ib2), please specify IP addresses in this file in the order of ib0, ib2.\nMoreover, please specify the NID based on the IP address in the second column as the NID in the first column.\nFor example, when 192.168.128.10 is specified in the second column, the first column should be set to 192.168.128.10@o2ib0\n\nAll nodes which have IB HCA in the system need to have this configuration file with unique contents.\n\n2. Starting lnet\n==============\nPlease start lnet by executing \"service lnet start\".\nThe setting of IB Multi-Rail will be done in the service script of lnet.\n\nChange-Id: I343a0f61d213dadcae73bdbe10b285a896449529\nSifned-off-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
